A special task team is now going to probe the cause of the incident. Advocate Myron Dewrance has been appointed to head up the team, which has a month to complete the task. eNCA's Khayelihle Khumalo reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The families of the six people who recently died in a Putco bus fire on Moloto Road are demanding the truth behind their loss.
A special task team is now going to probe the cause of the incident. Advocate Myron Dewrance has been appointed to head up the team, which has a month to complete the task. READ: Putco bus accident | Investigation underway The deceased were burnt beyond recognition and more than 50 passengers managed to escape. Government says it is hoping to understand what happened and prevent future incidents. eNCA’s Khayelihle Khumalo shares more details in the video above.